I"d<h3 id="1-put-all-your-packages-files-in-1-folder">1. Put all your package’s files in 1 folder</h3>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>📁your-package-name
├── 📁your-package-file-01
├── 📁your-package-file-02
└── 📁your-package-file-03
</code></pre></div></div>

<h3 id="2-create-a-packagejson-file">2. Create a <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">package.json</code> file</h3>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>📁your-package-name
├── 📁your-package-file-01
├── 📁your-package-file-02
├── 📁your-package-file-03
└── package.json
</code></pre></div></div>

<h3 id="3-edit-the-packagejson-file">3. Edit the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">package.json</code> file</h3>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>{
    "name": "your-package-name",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "description": "Write your package's description here.",
    "main": "your-package-name.js",
    "scripts": 
    {
        "test": "echo \"Error\" &amp;&amp; exit 1"
    },
    "keywords": 
    [
        "your-package-keyword"
    ],
    "author": "Your Name Here",
    "license": "MIT"
}
</code></pre></div></div>
